## Database Optimization

### Indexes
```ruby
# Always index foreign keys
add_index :articles, :user_id

# Index frequently queried columns
add_index :articles, :status
add_index :articles, :published_at

# Compound indexes for common queries
add_index :articles, [:user_id, :status]
```

### N+1 Queries
```ruby
# Bad: N+1 query
articles.each { |article| article.user.name }

# Good: Eager load
Article.includes(:user).each { |article| article.user.name }
```

### Counter Cache
```ruby
# Add counter cache column
add_column :users, :articles_count, :integer, default: 0

# Use in model
belongs_to :user, counter_cache: true

# Access without query
user.articles_count  # No database query!
```

